name: Mark Millar
bio:
President, Netflix's Millarworld Dept
Writer of Kingsman, The Chosen One, The Magic Order, Huck, Kick-Ass, Night Club & more.
Official Website ⬇️

social_posts.post_text: Too good not to share... :)
We're here if you need us.

Flying visit to Scotland over the weekend where my buddy Big Liam and I hired a small boat to take us to freezing cold, remote Scottish island to meet a retired broadcasting legend we're both in awe of. There's only one road on this island and 160 people, but they all seem great. Our host and his wife gave us as much lunch and booze as our bodies could handle and then we set sail back to the mainland. Just back home now!

ON SALE THIS WEEK! The antichrist is in the White House, the world is ravaged by war and pandemics and the micro-chipping of the human race has begun. Now Jesus returns to judge mankind and a 2000 year old promise is about to be kept. American Jesus #2 is in stores tomorrow, the Netflix adaptation also coming soon!
The Antichrist is in the White House. Heaven help us! American Jesus #2 in all good comic stores today. Art by Peter Gross. Cover by Muir. Story by that Michael Flately lookalike guy!
It might take me a year or two to get ahead on my schedule, but I'm 100% going to do a Superman story again at some point. I've had a notebook I've been noodling in for quite a while now...

The Hollywood Reporter just went live with my new project. This was four years in the making and combines six books over six different countries, each one drawn by a superstar creator. Frank Quitely. Karl Kerschl. Travis Charest. Olivier Coipel. Matteo Buffagni. Matteo Scalera. A whole new way of doing superheroes goes global in March.

Here's a fun fact: Did you know I've invested in a sizeable percentage of a London Soho Club? It's called BLACKS on Dean St and I chipped in with my friend when he acquired it recently. You can apply for membership on our website. Instagram doesn't allow links, but we're very easy to find online. Come in and have a drink!

Here's my two most prized geek possessions - Christopher Reeve's Superman cape and a Superman The Movie one-sheet signed by Brando, Reeve, Hackman, Richard Donner, Stamp, Kidder, Ned Beatty and Valerie Perrine. This took more effort than you might think!

Night Club #1 launches tomorrow and this is the Spawn variant from the brilliant @matteoscalera. I don't know why I'm posting this as it's already sold out, but sometimes it's just nice to see something and pore over some beautiful art! Only 24 hrs to go...

This month's hottest book is FINALLY HERE! NIGHT CLUB #1 by Mark Millar and @juananramirez is on sale now and only $1.99 a month! Also - Sign up to our free newsletter at the website in my bio this morning for an exclusive preview of #2!

MASSIVE MILLARWORLD 2023 preview coming on Wednesday 21st December. The only way to see this is to sign up to our free newsletter right now (link in bio). Nemesis variant cover by the great Frank Quitely. Note: Final orders for Nemesis: Reloaded issue 1 by me and @jorge_jimenez_art is this weekend!
Merry Christmas, gentle readers! Here's to an even cooler and more exciting 2023! Love from your #1 DILF!
Back in Scotland between Christmas and New Year. Epic pyjamas from Daughter No1!!!

Magic Order Volume 3 finale yesterday. Look at these amazing covers by @gigicavenago and @gregtocchini_art. Does Italy produce the best comic artists in the world right now? I really think so. It's been a privilege to work with you, Gigi. Can't wait to see your next project!

Millar
Buffagni
You'll love it.

What happens when the world's smartest man is up against an entire club of the world's smartest men?

Prodigy: The Icarus Society the complete collection is in stores this week.
One more day until @jorge_jimenez_art and I blow your minds. PS Type Millar Time into Youtube for a nice Nemesis surprise today. I know we can't do links here, but you'll like this...

To celebrate NEMESIS RELOADED #1 tomorrow, here's all four covers, including original series artist and co-creator @mcnivenart. The others are @fionastaples @frankquitelyofficial and of course our pal and artist for this 5 issue spectacular @jorge_jimenez_art

Today is the day.
Get down to that comic shop and TREAT yourself.
Nemesis Reloaded issue 1 by your favourite Scot and @jorge_jimenez_art.
ON SALE NOW.

Huge thanks to everyone for the SPECTACULAR response to NEMESIS RELOADED #1 last week. This week we have Night Club #2 and we think it's going to be mega as #1 just sold out, back to the printers tonight for anyone who missed it. On sale Wednesday! Buy one for your Mum!! PS Cover by the great @juananramirez!

NIGHT CLUB #2 is on sale today for $1.99! #1 is back the printers to meet demand so get in there now with the second issue so it's waiting for you when you read the first one. Art by @juananramirez and the scene when Danny starts biting his friends!!!
Thanks for all the Night Club #2 love this week, guys. Here's a peek at the evil SOB coming in #3 to spoil all the good times! Can this really just be $1.99 an issue? Oh yes!!

NEMESIS is back at the printers as we're totally sold out. Final Orders for this new cover by @JorgeJimenezArt
 is tomorrow. Don't you dare miss!!
On sale TODAY! A new Magic Order story and WITHOUT A DOUBT our most exciting ever. Art by mega-star @dikeruan!

It's been 19 years in the making, but today we get the GRAND FINALE to the American Jesus trilogy! My thanks to co-creator @petergrossart for being the perfect partner in this. We're very proud of this comic! PS Live action adaptation streaming on Netflix this year!
MANY THANKS to all you fine people for the amazing response to the new Magic Order story that started this week. The Magic Order Vol 4, art by @dikeruan. Isn't he something special? On sale now!

To celebrate the big finale to our comnic this week, here's a screenshot from Netflix's upcoming American Jesus show. You'll be able to watch the whole thing in just another few months, but now the entire three volume series has concluded this week you can jump ahead of your friends and SPOIL EVERYTHING for them. My wife and I watched the final cut of eps 1 and 2 yesterday and this is an absolute thing of beauty. You guys will love. The plot? A kid is taken to a small village by his mother and hidden from the world as she knows he's the returned Jesus Christ. Her plan is to keep him safe until he's older and able to face the Antichrist in the Battle of Armageddon. This comic took Peter Gross and I 19 years so it was pleased to see such great reviews this week when the final issue hit stands. Thanks all!

Just back from seeing this terrific play with Elizabeth McGovern, Dougray Scott, Charles Aitken and @georginapeggy. I love seeing a piece where everyone is at the peak of their powers. We were in there for over three and a half hours, but the audience was buzzing even as we were walking out. Go see this. It's an absolute beaut!
The Magic Order #2 is in stores TODAY! Art by the brilliant, brilliant @dikeruan. Story by yours truly!!!

Huge amount of love this week for the new issue of The Magic Order. Thanks to everyone on behalf of the team. @dikeruan is being singled out as an absolute superstar and rightly so. I've been asked to show some of his work in black and white or any behind the scenes stuff so check out his sketch for this month's issue. The guy's amazing.

Night Club & Nemesis Reloaded have sold out of every issue we printed. This weekend is your last chance to order The Ambassadors #1. Mark Millar & Frank Quitely. It doesn't get more Scottish than that!

THE AMBASSADORS is the best, most ambitious comic-book I've ever done and superstar artist FRANK QUITELY (All Star Superman) is launching it with me this month. Don't be left with a second printing of this beauty! This weekend is your last chance to order!

Mark Millar
Jorge Jiminez
On sale today.

Leave your morals at the door!

Thanks to everyone for the PHENOMENAL words on Nemesis Reloaded #3 this weekend. On behalf of @jorge_jimenez_art, myself and the team we're super thankful for all the lovely comments and can't wait for you to see where this goes. This thing is MENTAL!!! PS Magic Order #3 this week, The Ambassadors #1 next week. DID I MENTION THIS IS DRAWN BY FRANK QUITELY?!?!?!?!?!!
Me photobombing an otherwise nice pic last weekend. These are my wee cousins btw...
The best thing to happen this week just arrived - The Magic Order #3 is in stores NOW!
Wise words in the new Magic Order this week. Beautiful art by Dike Ruan!

More Dike Ruan goodness in this week's Magic Order #3. I just finished the fifth volume of this a few weeks back and we're deep in the Netflix show so this is pretty all consuming at the moment. Love that people are digging it so much!

To celebrate the release of The Ambassadors #1 this week by Mark Millar and FRANK QUITELY (!!!) we're sharing our variant cover for issue 1 by the amazing @pepelarraz. Note: This cover has already sold out at distributor level so if you didn't pre-order you absolutely won't get a copy. However, if you get to your store early enough on Wednesday you should get the phenomenal Quitely cover before it disppears.
Look at our OTHER gorgeous variant this week, this one by Italian maestro @gigicavenago. The Ambassadors #1 is out on Wednesday from MARK MILLAR and FRANK QUITELY!

Only one more day until THE AMBASSADORS lands. 

Mark Millar. Frank Quitely. 

YOU LOVE IT!

Coming soon: THE CHOSEN ONE, the @netflix adaptation of the American Jesus trilogy I created with artist & co-creator @PeterGrossArt. A little boy finds out he's the new Jesus Christ & will grow up to face the Antichrist in The Apocalypse. Official poster here.

The three books were just competed, by the way, and you can buy them in all good stores. Can you believe these took Peter and I almost 19 years?!?!

8 Billion people. 6 can have superpowers. Who do you choose?

The Ambassadors #1 is on sale today and we just had word from the distributor that it's sold out already and going back to press TONIGHT. This is Frank Quitely's first comic book in 6 years and people going crazy for it. Huge thank you to everyone for their enthusiasm and support. Mega thanks too for all those sterling reviews. You know we always love to read em!!! Cheers from the entire team and your favourite curly haired Scot!!
7 years before today's Ambassadors #1, here's Frank Quitely and I trying to sneak out of a Glasgow restaurant without paying. Photo by either Dave Gibbons or Goran Parlov!

Listen, I just want to say thank you to all for the SPECTACULAR launch and great reviews for The Ambassadors #1 yesterday. Sold out first day and a big second printing this weekend, which is great. Here's a wee look at Frank Quitely's variant cover for CODENAME INDIA in #2, on sale in just 13 days! Yes, this book really is out TWICE every month!

Family visiting the in-laws for a few days. So...
Pub booked for 2pm.
McDonalds Dinner planned for 8pm.
Now... a nice cuppa tea and the Sunday papers...
On sale this week - Night Club #4 for only $1.99! This is my favourite issue yet! And look at that @matteoscalera cover. He is a BEAST!!!!

At Brooks club in Pall Mall for lunch with pals yesterday, one of them picking up a new hat from @LockandCo across the road afterwards. Weird fact: This is the real-life store where @SamuelLJackson bought his top hat in Kingsman: The Secret Service.

Night Club #4 came out yesterday and a thanks from the team for all the kind words! If you ever wanted to see a superhero vampire save a baby from an exploding building this is your book!!!

Also: This is the first time in my life I've ever had 5 books out in same month... Night Club, Nemesis Reloaded, The Magic Order and TWO issues of The Ambassadors. Yes, #2 is out next week. The series is TWICE A MONTH!!!
A man from the future rung my doorbell last and brought me Millarworld comics from next Wednesday. How is that even possible?? @jorge_jimenez_art @karlkerschl
HAPPY EASTER! Up at 7am like it's Christmas morning and ran downstairs to eat my first chocolate in 6 weeks, like Renton in Trainspotting guzzling much missed drugs. Have a beaut, people!
There is nothing more glamorous to me than a motorway services mini Vegas in the English Midlands, right beside a Gregg’s…

Just back from a wee holiday in Scotland (amazing!), but wanted to drop a big thanks to all you sexy beasts before we put the kids to bed. It was great to see everyone loving Nemesis and The Ambassadors this week. We're working our socks off and glad you're all so into it!!! @karlkerschl @jorge_jimenez_art
The Ambassadors #3 is drawn by the legendary @travischarestart, a guy I've wanted to work with for half my life. You will not believe how good this looks. On sale in just ELEVEN DAYS TIME!!!!!!!

Superman 1st appeared 85 years ago today with Action Comics #1 & I was immediately reminded of being 13 & trying to woo a girl at school by showing her the Gil Kane/ Curt Swan art in the 45th Anniversary special. Narrators Voice: 'She wasn't that impressed.'

ABRACADABRA! The Magic Order #4 is out today from yours truly and 
@dike_ruan! Meet Cordelia's long lost older brother PERDITUS MOONSTONE!!!

Last week's Ambassadors #2 sold out in four hours, but fear not! We have a new printing comic with an extra eight pages of bonus material. Orders close this weekend. Have a word with your local retailer now and don't miss out again!!

We're going back to press YET AGAIN on Nemesis Reloaded #1 with 
@jorge_jimenez_art FOC will be May 8th and this will have some extra bits at the back. You only have yourselves to blame for encouraging us!

The Ambassadors #3 is probably the greatest comic ever drawn and you are now just two days away from holding it in your hands! @TravisCharest's first full comic in 24 years. This will sell out in 3 pico seconds!!
OK so my genius artist daughter @emilybrooksmillar just posted her portrait of Tony Hawk. And then THIS happened...

The first full-length comic by @TravisCharest in 24 years is in stores now. 

What are you waiting for? RUN!!!
We overprinted on Ambassadors #3, but only 400 copies left at the distributor on first few hours of release. Prepping a second edition right now. Glory be to the mighty @TravisCharest!
Ryan Sook's PHENOMENAL variant cover for The Ambassadors #4 (with a little teaser for Aussie Ambassador Big Bob Taylor in the background)...
The brilliant Javier Fernandez variant cover for tomorrow's big NEMESIS FINALE!!!
On behalf of the team, thank you for the phenomenal response to The Ambassadors #4. isn't Olivier Coipel the greatest man alive? 11 days until next issue and the AUSSIE Ambassador!!

Well, Nemesis Reloaded ending this week with a bang. A bang, a stab, an explosion and probably a castration. Would you expect anything less? Keep an eye out this Tuesday for all the stuff we've been hiding from you, teased in this finale, as we start to unpack BIG GAME, the mighty Millarworld crossover event of the summer. Nemesis, Kick-Ass, The Magic Order, Hit-Girl, Kingsman and The Chrononauts. IT'S ALL HERE! ON SALE JULY!!

Next week's Ambassadors #5 has my favourite character from the whole series- Aussie icon BIG BOB TAYLOR. He's a hard drinking, former rugby star who was also Australia's Deputy Prime Minister. He's an absolute beast and he steals this book!

Me
@pepelarraz
Big preview on CBR tomorrow.

PS read NEMESIS finale first!!

THE CHOSEN ONE is released on Netflix August 16th. This is the adaptation of Chosen, the first in the American Jesus trilogy I created with the brilliant artist @petergrossart. You don't want to miss this. It's absolutely beautiful. This isn't some cheesy comedy either. This is the Book of Revelation seen through a little boy who discovers he's the returned Jesus Christ and a huge destiny awaits him.

It's OFFICIAL! BIG GAME starts on July 19th from yours truly and MARVEL MEGASTAR @pepelarraz!!! This follows on directly from Nemesis Reloaded and brings Nemesis, Wanted's Wesley Hibson, Kick-Ass, Kingsman, The Magic Order and every single Millarworld franchise together into our first ever Summer mega-event. This is an absolute beauty so get your order in now!!!

The best issue yet of The Ambassadors hits stores today! #5 has art by the genius @matteo_buffagni and is the first appearance of Big Bob taylor, the no nonsense Aussie superhero, former Deputy Prime Minister and rugby legend. This guy is unlike any superhero you've ever seen before and he's AWESOME. Preview HERE:

https://www.amazon.co.uk/Ambassadors-5-Mark-Millar-ebook/dp/B0C3P87VSR?asin=B0C3P87VSR&revisionId=&format=2&depth=1

Night Club #5 is ON SALE TODAY! This is my fave issue of the series and contains the creepiest vampire scene ever written! Art by the brilliant @juananramirez. How can this be just $1.99 every month?!?!?!?!?!
Preview HERE:
https://www.amazon.co.uk/Night-Club-5-Mark-Millar-ebook/dp/B0BW1Y5JHL?asin=B0BW1Y5JHL&revisionId=&format=2&depth=1

Penultimate issue of Magic Order Volume 4 on sale today with #5 as Madame Albany's plan kicks into high gear while Cordelia Moonstone is trapped in a book with her evil older brother. Look at this cover by @dikeruan and look at this beautiful variant from @urbanbarbarian!!!

Huge day for Millarworld today as The Ambassadors finale lands in stores with Magic Order #5. We've had @frankquitelyofficial , @karlkerschl , @travischarestart, @oliviercoipel and @matteo_buffagni twice a month since March. Now it's the mighty Italian Stallion they call @matteoscalera upfront and this issue is DOUBLE SIZED. We hope you love it. Leave all comments below and don't forget - This leads directly into BIG GAME, the huge Millarworld crossover starting next month from @pepelarraz and I!!
Beautiful variant cover for Big Game #1 by the phenomenal Jae Lee. Orders must be in next week. Crossover event begins next month!

Want to see the rest of these variant covers for Big Game #1? Nip over to @cbr right now and feast yer peepers on Frank Quitely, Danny Earls and more! This book launches July 19th and will be drawn by X-Men superstar @pepelarraz !!
Sitting here thinking which creator I steal from Marvel and DC today...

ON SALE LAST WEEK!
Yes, I'm just back from my holidays and so this is a week late going up. But it's finally here - The sequel to Wanted and starring ALL THE MILLARWORLD CHARACTERS from Kick-Ass and Hit-Girl to The Magic Order and Nemesis. Best off all? DRAWN BY THE HANDSOME SPANISH DEVIL THEY CALL PEPE LARRAZ!!!!
ON SALE TODAY! NIGHT CLUB #6—the stunning conclusion to the first arc of your new favourite book. DOUBLE SIZED FINALE!!
One of these will be murdered by Nemesis in Big Game #2 and you know I'm crazy enough that NOBODY is safe! Who will it be??

HOLA! Our new show, The Chosen One, dropped a couple of days back, but my wife and I were on a break and I really am the last man on Earth without a mobile phone. So here we are three days in and the show is not only number 2 in Mexico, but number 8 GLOBALLY which is pretty crazy. Our plan was to go hard in the Spanish speaking territories and then English language later, but great word of mouth seems to be doing this for us. Huge thanks to the Gout Bros for doing the most amazing job with this adaptation of our American Jesus books and also our brilliant cast, who honestly could not be better. Thanks to everyone and PLEASE don't spoil the big finale!! :)

Also out this past week, the grand finale for The Magic Order volume 4. Look at this art by Dike Ruan! Madame Albany is back! Edgar has escaped from the castle. Most of the Magic Order has been murdered. How THE HELL does Cordelia save the day?????

OK, we're now #3 in the world!! It's a little too early to talk about miracles, but jumping up five places in a single day is some pretty damn good word of mouth when all our advertising was aimed exclusively at the Latin American market. What I love is if this works we will see more big genre shows coming out of other markets and not just everything set in New York City. @pacoramosq runs the best department at Netflix. He should take a bow here! Thanks to everyone involved in this show and to you guys for supporting it!!

President, Netflix's Millarworld Dept
